        Q("VPN Essentials", '''<p>A VPN encrypts all traffic and hides your IP address. Essential for torrenting: your IP is visible to everyone in the swarm. Choose a no-log VPN: Mullvad (anonymous, €5/mo), ProtonVPN (free tier, Swiss), AirVPN (port forwarding for private trackers), IVPN (audited no-log). Kill switch: bind your torrent client to the VPN interface (qBittorrent: Settings > Advanced > Network Interface) — if the VPN drops, your traffic stops.</p>'''),
        Q("Operational Security", '''<p>Opsec: use a separate browser profile for piracy (Firefox Multi-Account Containers), enable uBlock Origin (block malware ads), don't log into personal accounts, use a fake email for forum registrations, avoid clicking "download" buttons on shady sites — use JDownloader2 instead. Scan every downloaded .exe/.msi on VirusTotal before running. Real-Debrid: cached torrents stream from their servers, your IP never hits the swarm.</p>'''),
