        Q("The *Arr Stack", '''<p>The *Arr stack automates media downloading and organization. Sonarr (TV shows — search, download, organize, rename), Radarr (movies — same as Sonarr for films), Lidarr (music), Readarr (books), Bazarr (subtitles), Prowlarr (indexer manager — syncs to all *Arrs). Installation: Docker-compose is easiest — linuxserver.io maintains all *Arr images. Each app has a web UI on a different port (e.g., :8989 for Sonarr).</p>'''),
